<qandaset>
<question>
<para>What are the most common corporate entities? Is a formal offer procedure
required for the acquisition of any of these? </para>
</question>
<answer jurisdiction="UK">
<para>The limited liability company (either a private limited company (Ltd)
or a public limited company (plc) (which can offer shares to the public and
have its shares listed on a stock exchange) ), A plc must have a minimum share
capital of &pound;50,000 (US$75,000),  </para>
</answer>
<answer jurisdiction="USA">
<para>The most common form of corporate entity is the corporation. There is
no minimum share capital. Generally speaking, corporations are either public
or closely-held, in which case different tax and corporate law provisions
may apply. </para>
</answer>
